SIMPLE: antiphony
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Antiphony
<hw>An*tiph"o*ny</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Antiphonies</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[See
<er>Antiphon</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A musical response; also,
antiphonal chanting or signing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An anthem or psalm sung alternately by a choir or
congregation divided into two parts. Also figuratively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O! never more for me shall winds intone,⟦br⟧
With all your tops, a vast <qex>antiphony</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>R.
Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antiphrasis</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
